Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove the @confit duck legs{2} from their packaging. Place onto a lined #baking tray{}, skin-side up.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven for ~{25-30%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Ensure the duck is piping hot throughout.

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a medium #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While everything cooks, trim and thinly slice the @radishes{100%g}. Zest and halve the @lime{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, add half the lime juice, the @sugar{1%tsp} for the pickle. Stir through the radish.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and set aside to pickle.

Trim the @pak choi{1}, then thinly slice widthways. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the pak choi and stir-fry until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds} more.

Transfer to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm. Set the pan aside for later.

Once cooked, transfer the duck to a #plate{}. Use two #forks{} to shred the duck as finely as you can. Discard the bones.

Return the (now empty) pan to medium-high heat. Add the @teriyaki sauce{75%g}, @soy sauce{15%ml} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce. Bring it to a boil and stir through the duck.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it. Add a splash of water if needed.

Fluffy up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest. Share between your serving bowls.

Top the rice with the teriyaki duck, pickled radish and garlic pak choi in separate sections.

Sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g} and serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!